efines the allowable range of azimuth (which refers to the horizontal angle) around the centroid of the focus object."], "extent": [1670, 1806]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "azimuth_max"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}, {"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 4, "text": ["Distance and Screen Percentage"], "extent": [1806, 1849], "body": [{"type": "parameters_item_group", "body": [{"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Screen Percentage Min"], "extent": [1849, 1877], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Defines the allowable minimum percentage of screen space an object can occupy along the smaller of the two screen space axes, determined by the camera\u2019s aspect ratio."], "extent": [1904, 2088]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "screenpct_min"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Screen Percentage Max"], "extent": [2088, 2115], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Defines the allowable maximum percentage of screen space an object can occupy along the smaller of the two screen space axes, determined by the camera\u2019s aspect ratio."], "extent": [2142, 2326]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "screenpct_max"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Enable Distance Range Min"], "extent": [2326, 2357], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Enables the use of a custom distance range. If this box is not checked the camera dome will default to an automatic range calculation based on the object size and the cameras, aperture and focal length settings. Depending on the cameras aspect ratio the auto distance will calculate by either the horizontal aperture or vertical aperture, whichever aperture is smaller."], "extent": [2390, 2777]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "enabledistrange_min"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Distance Range Min"], "extent": [2777, 2801], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Defines the allowable minimum range for the camera\u2019s distance from the centroid of the focus object."], "extent": [2828, 2946]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "distrange_min"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Enable Distance Range Max"], "extent": [2946, 2977], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Enables the use of a custom distance range. If this box is not checked the camera dome will default to an automatic range calculation based on the object size and the cameras, aperture and focal length settings. Depending on the cameras aspect ratio the auto distance will calculate by either the horizontal aperture or vertical aperture, whichever aperture is smaller."], "extent": [3010, 3397]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "enabledistrange_max"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Distance Range Max"], "extent": [3397, 3421], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Defines the allowable maximum range for the camera\u2019s distance from the centroid of the focus object."], "extent": [3448, 3566]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "distrange_max"}, "role": "item"}, {"type": "parameters_item", "indent": 4, "text": ["Maintain Object Screen Percentage"], "extent": [3566, 3605], "body": [{"type": "para", "indent": 8, "text": ["Distributes cameras to achieve an equal distribution of the focus object\u2019s screen space size, rather than equalizing the distances between the focus object and the camera. Useful when there is significant variation in camera distance."], "extent": [3631, 3883]}], "container": true, "attrs": {"id": "objscreenpct"}, "role": "item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group"}]}]}, {"level": 2, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 4, "text": ["Camera"], "extent": [3883, 3900], "body": [{"level": 3, "id": null, "container": true, "type": "h", "indent": 4, "text": ["Pri